            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--Opens with a latin acclamation to Eumeni Vivas. The rest in Greek; cf. IG 14.1078 for similar; Eumenius Alpinius Magnus. Extensive discussion of likely career / origins (apparently a citizen of Lilybaeum, but p'haps of Gallic origin?), relating it to Chastagnol, Historia 12 (1963) and consularis governors of the island between 320 and 331 AD. Cf. CIL 10.517 for this man as gov. of Lucania and Bruttium in 320s. Note p.233: 'Non mancano iscrizioni greche dedicate, in Italia e talora in altre regioni, a funzionari di diocesi italiche...' Goes through Chastagnol for e.g.s, which incl. IG 14.453=CIL 10.7017; IG 14.1075 = CIL 6.1715; IG 14.455; IG 14.14 = CIL 10.7125; CIL 6.31961 = IG 14.1078a. Section in Greek: Alpeinion Magnon ton lamprotaton hupatikon kai hagnotaton dikasten boule kai demos Lilubaeiton dia tas peri ten patrida euergesias ton patrona emipsato. Discussions of relevance in Kokalos 1982-83 (38-39) 472 and Kokalos (1997-1998) 43-44.1: 253--></p>
            </div>
